<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_85b59343-204c-4b2b-b563-b6313d16ba56" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>7.5.4</sptc><title id="_6e35155d-2f14-42f7-bfa6-326987414240">Sheet wall cladding</title><archive-num>2019: 3.5.4.4</archive-num><subclause id="_6227a1d2-1208-4eed-ac61-d3ed901d0445" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_0f31dec8-3148-47cf-a852-c276a876333c">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Fibre-cement sheet wall cladding must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_eb37bb47-8b4f-4af1-9543-e900ca50b05e">comply with AS/NZS 2908.2 or ISO 8336; and</li><li id="_13730cdb-efea-4b65-a9d0-e9e2a1f01970">be fixed in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/419_1.2.0.xml#_9c7ff7bf-a67e-4ed9-a786-2b35b2b5c0d9" id="_ba3adbac-1e00-4bfb-8c74-a658905e77c7" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 7.5.4a</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_b5839d24-dd2b-4d4f-9339-63b8b694e48a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ff2b81c4-2d3d-4c03-b3d9-fb9f364ec2f7">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Hardboard sheet wall cladding must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_09f99f29-05c2-4da3-83bf-1729648515f2">comply with AS/NZS 1859.4 for exterior grade; and</li><li id="_43de436b-a522-42a3-a162-06f2a97ddffe">be fixed in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/420_1.2.0.xml#_9d6adbdd-57d4-4a69-9900-2f6fbf6fce7d" id="_00edbce8-4ec9-4f3e-b9d0-5e7cca226c36" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 7.5.4b</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_baa40d62-07c6-4036-8a39-5fc6b8e4a0f9" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_62a8229d-985b-4879-a720-f886532f642a">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Structural plywood wall cladding must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_051d9c29-90e2-41bb-85fe-a2141336f639">comply with AS/NZS 2269.0; and</li><li id="_5f149a66-5fd6-4047-92ce-df552b7d30a8">be fixed in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/421_1.2.0.xml#_c8ff4bba-036e-4be9-ae98-144968c9ece6" id="_02824ac9-ef88-4bb3-9849-732125b4330e" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 7.5.4c</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/419_1.2.0.xml" graph="None" id="_9c7ff7bf-a67e-4ed9-a786-2b35b2b5c0d9"><num>7.5.4a</num><title id="_f766f9e8-c986-4d8e-9152-a2cf28027caf">Stud and fixing spacings for 6 mm fibre-cement sheet wall cladding</title><table id="_8aa55b0b-cfd2-4ac6-8e5f-8a54108bee96" keycol="1"><tgroup cols="4"><colspec colname="001" colnum="1" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="002" colnum="2" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="003" colnum="3" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="004" colnum="4" colwidth="108.00*"/><thead><row><entry>Wind class</entry><entry>Maximum stud spacing (mm)</entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing within 1.2 m of the external corners of the building (mm) <sup id="_4cfd6645-dc5a-45fe-8026-90498e0fc2fa">Note 1</sup></entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing elsewhere (mm) <sup id="_8799d9c0-56ab-47ee-bad7-6915dd72d13b">Note 1</sup></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>N1</entry><entry>≤ 1.2 m of external building corners: 600 Elsewhere: 600</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 200</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 200</entry></row><row><entry>N2</entry><entry>≤ 1.2 m of external building corners: 600 Elsewhere: 600</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 200</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 200</entry></row><row><entry>N3</entry><entry>≤ 1.2 m of external building corners: 450 Elsewhere: 600</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 200</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 200</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><desc-note id="_257655b7-ca39-4dab-a173-4e6a5937f052"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_e1fca9f3-da01-48d2-9bb2-ce81ba8eab48">Maximum nail spacing using 2.8 mm fibre-cement nails.</li><li id="_cacb3f3a-0227-4c7a-8465-d8707e0b58eb">Fixings must be located not less than 50 mm from the edge of all corners.</li><li id="_fe98eca7-86d3-4276-9494-65bbefb85514">Fasteners must penetrate not less than 30 mm into a timber frame.</li><li id="_06e18485-0fbf-4080-b1ec-ca8169501d76">Wall cladding may be fixed through timber or metal battens attached to the wall frame in accordance with AS 1684.2, AS 1684.3, AS 1684.4 or NASH standard as appropriate (see fixing requirements for roof battens) so long as the minimum penetration into the wall frame is achieved.</li></ol></desc-note></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/420_1.2.0.xml" graph="None" id="_9d6adbdd-57d4-4a69-9900-2f6fbf6fce7d"><num>7.5.4b</num><title id="_5b999818-d92a-4bcc-a570-ef4b119c4067">Stud and fixing spacings for 9.5 mm thick hardboard sheet wall cladding</title><table id="_48ae5d65-b4c8-4b13-a2fc-87451375e3a6" keycol="1"><tgroup cols="4"><colspec colname="001" colnum="1" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="002" colnum="2" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="003" colnum="3" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="004" colnum="4" colwidth="108.00*"/><thead><row><entry>Wind class</entry><entry>Maximum stud spacing (mm)</entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing within 1.2 m of the external corners of the building (mm) <sup id="_3ee94ed9-b52e-46a9-aea7-b32fb7f91686">Note 1</sup></entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing elsewhere (mm) <sup id="_4090aa5a-741c-444f-aa70-b7f0949423c6">Note 1</sup></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>N1</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry></row><row><entry>N2</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry></row><row><entry>N3</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry><entry>Body: 300, Edges: 150</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><desc-note id="_2d759921-8418-477d-954c-d8856f6da4a9"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_4c79238f-7046-4e28-90bb-702d3cd71e33">Maximum nail spacing using 2.8 mm galvanised clouts or flat head nails.</li><li id="_066668c1-3268-48d2-a2ec-00d3370018cd">Fixings must be positioned a minimum of 12 mm from the edge of the sheet and not less than 50 mm from the edge of all corners.</li><li id="_2746ce78-a3b4-41e0-93ba-a142624faafb">Fasteners must penetrate not less than 30 mm into the timber frame.</li><li id="_63bdd793-714e-41ad-a5c9-214698723c7b">Wall cladding may be fixed through timber or metal battens attached to the wall frame in accordance with AS 1684.2, AS 1684.3, AS 1684.4 or NASH standard as appropriate (see fixing requirements for roof battens) so long as the minimum penetration into the wall frame is achieved.</li></ol></desc-note></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/421_1.2.0.xml" graph="None" id="_c8ff4bba-036e-4be9-ae98-144968c9ece6"><num>7.5.4c</num><title id="_3b77de60-dfe4-4f10-a843-cf50e0a9962d">Stud and fixing spacings for plywood wall cladding equal to or greater than 6.5 mm thick</title><table id="_1dd11c9b-2ec3-4998-baf7-c4ec8a8807ca" keycol="1"><tgroup cols="4"><colspec colname="001" colnum="1" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="002" colnum="2" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="003" colnum="3" colwidth="108.00*"/><colspec colname="004" colnum="4" colwidth="108.00*"/><thead><row><entry>Wind class</entry><entry>Maximum stud spacing (mm)</entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing within 1.2 m of the external corners of the building (mm) <sup id="_c8387225-c994-4667-bc3b-198175836100">Note 1</sup></entry><entry>Maximum nail spacing elsewhere (mm) <sup id="_471b1341-5ced-43c5-990d-1356a6bc58d0">Note 1</sup></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>N1</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 100</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 150</entry></row><row><entry>N2</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 100</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 150</entry></row><row><entry>N3</entry><entry>600</entry><entry>Body: 150, Edges: 100</entry><entry>Body: 200, Edges: 150</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><desc-note id="_0ab63257-297b-4b2e-9636-638af3fbe290"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_90ec50be-55a1-4253-8c10-9cc87a6cf132">Maximum nail spacing using 2.8 mm or 3.5 mm galvanised clouts or flat head nails. </li><li id="_a0fbc60f-9968-42e0-88af-8515221a3958">Fixings must be positioned a minimum of 12 mm from the edge of the sheet and not less than 50 mm from the edge of all corners.</li><li id="_b4deaefe-f1bf-41fe-bded-0c490151e8ec">Fasteners must penetrate not less than 30 mm into the timber frame</li><li id="_7a918c52-0d3f-41c7-b852-54bbb7480921">Wall cladding may be fixed through timber or metal battens attached to the wall frame in accordance with AS 1684.2, AS 1684.3, AS 1684.4 or NASH standard as appropriate (see fixing requirements for roof battens) so long as the minimum penetration into the wall frame is achieved.</li></ol></desc-note></table-reference><callout id="_9c5e19da-b848-4628-9a4e-bfe153e93f3e"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Where sheet bracing is also acting as structural bracing, fixing requirements are listed in AS 1684 and NASH Standard – Residential and Low-Rise Steel Framing, Part 2.</p></callout></clause>